<div id="p248" class="blockpost roweven">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#8&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=248#p248">16-Sep-2010,Thu 08:15:41</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=3">higopi</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Expert Member</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"><img src="img/avatars/3.jpg" width="60" height="60" alt="" /></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: Regarding Indian Scripts in Java Web Application</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Hi,<br /><br />By searching on the web I have found out the ML_Nila series fonts is using Unicode Encoding.<br /><br />So,<br /><br />1) The collation set should be utf_unicode_ci (Be careful, you may loose the existing data when you change the collation) - Also, make sure all the Malayalam data written in the database uses Unicode encoding.<br />2) As the font is Using Unicode encoding, you need to set the above collation set.<br />3) The directory specified in .getResourceAsStream()&nbsp; should be relative to current directory (where you place all your java/class code) or it should be relative to CLASSPATH</p>
				</div>
				<div class="postsignature"><hr />Thanks,<br /><br />Gopi<br />Pick any two of &quot;Quality, Quick, Cheap&quot; service from me.</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
